description: Dimensions: EL 102mm; EWe 44mm; W Body at break 23.2mm; EB fg. 19.5mm,Wt. 252.5 gms,Typology: traces of orig. mediial ridge on bl. faces; 'U' shield ridge; hint of bump - prob. stop on one face, not defineable,Manufacture: cavities in one fg. - pore holes?; v. sl. traces of line of cg. fl;,Condition: central part of e. blunt - poss. just corr. dam; both bl. corners broken - pres in ant - dusty corr. surs. with embedded soil; haft break also corr. sur. with embedded soil; fg. crests prob. old  dam. badly from corr.,Attached Material: yellow fawn soil traces

collection: Hampshire Co. Mus. Service,ex-Zillwood, Mr. M.A. - private (no. 10)
surface: Grass green patina over parts of one face and one side, mainly lost on rev. face and side; pocking to light green dry sur. and some lumpy corr.
description: Dimensions: EL 135.5mm; EWbl 23.3mm; EBfg 23.3mm; Bst 14mm; Wt. 338.4 gms,Typology: travesl of sl. central ridge on bl. faces descending from 'U' shield - sl. emphasised ridge; bump stop dipped in centre, as also sep. floor; stop on rev. was prob. placed lower,Manufacture: depression near base of rev. sep - cg. flaw; traces of broad low flattened cg. ft. on fg. sides - prob. fully removed on bl. sides to double facet.,Condition: both corners of bl. broken in ant - breaks dustry corr. sur. with soil embedded; main break with 2 facets - gold flecked, recent rubbing?; central part of e. also but blunt; butt end all broken sur.- dusty corr. and soil; all fg. crests dam.- anc. dam and corr. - except tiny stretch of one fg.; much of design detail lost through deterioration.,Attached material: yellow-brown soil traces
remarks: PIF; AFI; DF S; SI; CI; Rec. SN Jan 79,Source Sb A,Sub. Inf. Zillwood, 78 Sept.

collection: Hampshire Co. Museum Service,ex-Zillwood, Mr. M.A. - private (no. 9)
surface: Black green patina; [occ?] large pittings - light green dry surface. Few light green lumpy corr.; break at e. finely laminated light green structure - soil embedded
description: DImensions: EL 150.7mm; EWbt 21.7mm; Bfg 31mm; Bst 15mm; Wt. 413.5 gms,Typology: one bl. face with sl. fgs; sl. central rib and one diverging rib - more hints of 2 ribs on left hand side; rev. face with medial ridge only; sl. bumps for stops; shield hollow enclosed only by rounded bev.; sep. floor dipped in middle; fgs with rounded crests,Manufacture: Much of cg. fl still emphasised ridge/rib - prob some forging of top, but crests parts lost by corr., may have been jagged; cg. fl. stump along bl. and also diffuse e. bev. - esp. on one face -  not sharpening - cast; undulation in sep. floor - defect?; small irreg. ridges of metal across top bev.; on inside of one fg.; and perp. to bl. e. - cg. defects; dimples and 'flow' pattern  on sides,Condition: [?] e. break dusty corr. sur. - anc. break rather than miscast - on rev. face long straight ? scored groove borders break - marks divide between p. and laminated corr. structure; most of butt grey dry surface with embedded soil - anc. break, one corner copper brown; crest of one fg. badly chipped - prob. mainly recent - [?ring] of corr. layers exposed; fgs. otherwise little dam.; strs. prob. all recent,Attached Material: Yellowy-green thin coating matrix in places - soil? fawn soil in a few places.
remarks: PIF; AFI; DF S; SI; Rec. SN Jan 79; Source Sb A; Sub. Inf. Zillwood Sept 78

collection: Hampshire Co. Mus. Service,ex-Zillwood, Mr. M.A. - private (no. 8)
surface: Mottled dark to milky green, scattered limps of brightish green corr. assoc'd with pocks; breaks at edge, butt, and one fg. grey-coloured dry sur.
description: Dimensions: EL 136mm; EWe 48.5mm; EWbt 20.9mm; Bfg 29.6mm; Tsep 8.5mm; Bst 13mm; Wt. 372.1 gms,Typology: rounded medial ridge on bl faces, with concave flanking on one face, stems from rounded 'V' shield rib joining fg. bases; shield encloses sloped surface below ledge - stop - rounded; three short-thin ribs meet ledge on one face; sep. v. sl. dished with crisp side angles; fg. crests narrow and prob. mainly rounded; neat flattened vert. bars across base of fg. sides,Manufacture: no trace of cg. gls - fully removed, and bl. sides forged concave; hmks and dimples on sides and bl. faces, no extant e. bev.,Condition: all edge broken - anc. no sign of corr. dam.; butt break pale grey coloured dry sur. - prob. anc. as a small traves of soil embedded, parts of fgs broken - prob. in ant., but also some corr. dam. and modern rubbing - gold glecked; some striction down rev. bl. face - recent cleaning,Attached Material: Small traces of yellowy brown soil.
remarks: PIF; AFI; DF S; SI; CI; Rec. SN Jan 79; Source Sb A; Sub. Inf. Zillwood sept. 78

collection: Hampshire Co. Mus. Service,ex-Zillwood, Mr. M.A. - private (No. 7)
surface: dark fir green patina over much of one face and sides; few lumps of light green corr., much pocked to sim. colour dusty sur.
description: Dimensions: EL 141.2mm; EWst 22.3mm; EBfg 24.5mm; minBst 15mm; Wt. 389.6 gms,Typology: rounded medial ridges on bl. faces; descending from 'U' shaped ridge enclosing shallow depression; stop bump dips markedly from fgs to centre where a furrow produces a further notch; 3 ribs in one sep. - traces of at least 2 in rev. sep.; narrow nearly rounded fg. crests.,Manufacture: broad low flattened stump of cg. fl on fg. sides - almost a facet; ground awaoy on bl. sides to neat double facet; hint of former e. bev close to present bl. e. - undulations in sep. floors - cg. defects?; few dimples on fg. sides; small [?] on inside of one fg. - defect prob.,Condition: all of edge missing - all corroded sur., much pres anc. dam.; all of butt appears broken/corroded, also two reverse fgs much reduced; one abv. fg with notch - light gold colour; gmks in places - mainly recent cleaning,Attached Material: Orangey-fawn soil in odd patches
remarks: PIF; AFI; DF S; SI; CI; Rec. SN Jan 79; Source Sb. A; Sub. Inf. Zillwood Sept 78

collection: Hampshire Co. Mus. Service,ex-Zillwood, Mr. M.A. - private (no. 6)
surface: Mottled dark to grass green patina over much; areas flaked/pocked to dirty pale green; some brighter green lumpy corr.; coppery brown sur. at point of e. break; light gold along fg. break - hints of gold along other lower fg.
description: Dimensions: EL 147.2mm; EWbt 26.5mm; EBfg 32mm; Bst 18.5mm; Wt. 503.4 gms,Typology: Slight  median ridge on bl. faces - descendind from "U" shield shaped emphasised ridge on rev.; prob. near triang. shield on obverse despite corr. dam.; near flat tops to fg. crests; stops are emphasised ridges - dipped in centre; sl. rounded sep angles; orig. crinoline bl. shape,Manufacture: flattened stumps of cg. fls. on fg. sides - little lipping; removed to bevel on bl. sides; some hammer rippling of bl. faces and sides - fragment of e. bev. intact; all hmks on fg. sides; moulding dimples on bl. faces and sep.; central moulding depression within either sheild,Condition: most broken with corr dam. and pres. anc.; part near orig. line but blunt - corr. c hipped; butt broken off in ant.; virt. whole of one fg. broken off prob.  in ant. but now light gold - ?polished; remaining fgs. little chipped by corr.,Attached material: traces fawn soil in sep and in butt end.
remarks: PIF;AFI;S;SI;CI;Rec. SN Dec. 78; Source SbA; Sub Inf. Zillwood Sept 78

collection: Hampshire Co. Mus. service,ex-Zillwood, Mr. M.A. - private (no. 5)
surface: Grass green patina intact over much of one face, mostly flaked elsewhere to dull green dry sur. with lumpy light blue-green dusty corr.
description: Dimensions: EL 146.5mm; EWbt 24.6mm; maxEBfg. 27.4mm; minBst 22.8mm; Tsep 7.5mm; Wt. 384.2 gms,Typology: central rib on bl. faces; triang. flanking hollows at top; one stop markedly dipped in centre - not dam. - cg. flaw? possibly was some flattening of narrow fg. crests; rounded bump high across one sep.; this flat undercut end floored with bowed end; rev. sep. with more rounded floor and 2 short ribs in bowed end.,Manufacture: traces of cg. ft. as rounded rib or compromised ridge; rev. fl. little off-centre to left; few prob. moulding dimples on sides; depression between deep stumps - cg. flaw? faint hmks near edge - but no defined bevel.,Condition: Large bl. corner lost - prob. anc. and corr. dam; rest of e. irreg. from corr. chipping; butt end broken? and corr. dam.; chips in fg. crests - some poss anc., but also corr.; loop presumably broken in ant - one stump rubbed to dull copper; corners of rev. stop crest dam. by corr.; much of rev. dec. lost.,Attached Material: light yellowy fawn soil in pockets; remains of the casting of darker rich brown matrix
remarks: PIF, AFI; S; SI; CI; SN Jan 79; Source So.A; Sub. Inf. Zillwood, Sept. 78

collection: Hampshire Co. Mus. Service,ex-Zillwood, Mr. M.A. - private (no. 4)
surface: Grass green patina - much flaked and pitted; dull green with rusty orange staining on rev. bl. face - pitted sur.; elsewhere pale light-green dusty sur., odd lumps pale green corr.; one sep. covered with granular textured blue-green - speckled in odd other places.
description: Dimensions: EL 146mm; EWe 48.3mm; EWbt 22.3mm; Bst/fg junction 25mm; Tsep 8.2mm; Wt 379.5 gms,Typology: central ribs on near flat bl. faces, flanked by triang. hollow at top; one stop crest dipped in centre and with groove-cum-ridge along it - cast, but also some hammering; fg. crests were prob. rounded; fairly angular, sq. ended sep. one face; rev. sep with more rounded floor and 2 short ribs in end - not symm.; bt. top prob. flat orig.,Manufacture: depression between loop stumps - flow or design?; traces of cg. fl. - off central on rev. side, sligt dislocation between parts of the two valves, ? miscast stop (see above); no e. bev. survives,Condition: all bl. e. blunt - one bl. tip certainly ancient, rest corr. dam.; fg. crests irreg. due to corr. dam.; loop prob. lost in ant.- but recent rubbing to dull gold on stumps; bt. corr. dam - line poss. little changed.,Attached Material: Light yellow-brown soil matrix in pockets.

collection: Hampshire Co.. Museum Service,ex-Zillwood, Mr. M.A. - private (no. 3)
patina: Mottled dark to grass green patina over much; rest badly flaked or lumpy corr. to pale bluey - green dry surface.
description: Dimensions: EL 156mm; Wbt 24.7mm; Bfg 29.5mm; minBst 27.2mm; Tsep 7.6mm; Wt. 425.1 gms,Typology: very slight central ridge on bl.; more prom. and neat on rev. - upper parts flattened and flanked by triang. hollows - not sym.; stop crests flattened - not regular, fg. crests rounded where intact; bl. sides double facetted; one sep. floor more rounded than other; diffuse bev. at top of sep; one sep end with one definite short rib - rev. with prom. one to left. and poss. other(s),Manufacture: Pronounced hammer rippling of bl. faces, less prom. on sides;  no definite e bev - bit diffuse one on rev. face; small porosity hollow in one sep. end; some gmks across bl. e. may be ancient; stump of cg. fl only evid between loop stumps - fully removed elsewhere on intact sides,Condition: bl. e. all lost through corr. dam. - poss. previous dam. also; most of break pale green, but one tip grey-green - poss. just p. flaked; presumed loop stumps now just corroded lumps; most of butt lost, little poss. near intact; part of fg. crests little corr. dam; crevice in patina below one top - prob. recent dam.,Attached Material: small traces of yello to yellow-brown soil

collection: Hampshire Co. Museum Service,ex-Zillwood, Mr. M.A. -private (no. 2)
surface: Grassy green patina - slightly mottled shades intact over much; corr. lumps and bad pocking scattered - bluey-green
description: Dimensions: EL 157.2mm; EWe 48.2mm; EWbt 25.2mm; EBfg. 28.3mm; MinTst. 27mm (+?); T sep 7.5mm; Wt. 445.6 gms,Typology: central raised ridge on bl. flanked at top by triang.; diffuse bev at top of sep. hollows and where surviving stop and fg. crests tend to be flattened; bl sides recently double facetted; on sep. floor more rounded in cross section than other - sub. rect. ends with traces of 2 short ribs (left one prom. on one face),Manufacture: little dimpling of fg. sides prob from moulding; stumps of cg. fls on upper sides; fully removed on blade (where gmks mainly longitudinal - poss. recent); remnants of e. bev and hmks on lower blade; some tr. of flow ripples in rev. sep,Condition: loop broken in ant.; central part of blade edge probably just corr. chipped - rest were substantially damaged - poss. partly in ant.; part of bl. outline lost through corr.; crests on one face badly damaged - rev. fg. and dec virtually intact; rest of scmks prob. recent.,Attached material: yellow brown soil matrix in patches - parts richer ochre-brown

collection: Hampshire Co. Mus. Service,Ex-Zillwood, Mr. M.A. - private (no. 1),52 Porteous Crescent, Chandlers Ford, Eastleigh, Hampshire
surface: Dull green patina, slightly shiny, intact over much; scattered pocking and lumpy corr.; pale bluey-green - concentrated one side esp.; broken edge and butt surfaces similar pale green dusty surface.
description: Dimensions: EL 149mm; Wbt 24.2mm; Bfg 29mm; Blp 5.4mm; minBst. 27.1mm; Tsep 8.6mm,Wt. 437.2 gms,Typology: central raised ridge on blade flanked at top by triangular hollows - not wholly sym.; where preserved fg and st. crests flattened neatly; blade sides neatly shaped to double facet; rounded step-angles and sub-sect. end; shallowness of loop orig. feature; traces of three ribs in sep end - one more prom.; 2 or 3 in rev. sep.,Manufacture: dimpling od parts of fg. sides and lower blade - prob. from cg.; curved flow lines/ripples across seps; small stumps of cg. fls on haft sides - fully removed to bevel on bl.; remnant of e. bev. on largest part of bl,Condition. While of edge and butt end product of corr. damage - pale green dusty surfaces; 3 fg crests with variable corr. dam - prob only one significantly reduced; loop form lost; gmks prob. all recent,Attached Material: yellowy soil matrix in small patches.

description: Dimensions: EL 162.2mm; Wbl 28.6mm; W neck 1.07; Wsm 19.5; B sm 19.9; Blp 4.0; Wt. 66.1 g,Typology: dagger-shaped blade - only minimally altered by damage; traces of c. bev. very diffuse - no definite signs on the broadest part; midridge rounded on socket, becoming sharper towards tip; socket wall tapers quickly to sharp rim at mouth.,Manufacture: only remnants of cd. flash in form of small bumps above and below loops,Condition: tip lacking; blade edges sharp and parts a little serrated - due to surface loss; base of blade becomes rounded close to socket; number of perforations in socket wall evidently due to erosion - but some could have been thinly cast spots, or even cg. flaws, originally; one loop pres. eroded in middle.,Attached Material: lower socket completely blocked with fine sand and shells
remarks: Archive: PIF,PRBAF; DF(S); SI,Ext.: RSO 16/6/82; CI,Rec.: SN May 83,Source: Sb.A.
